duties:
1 - Teach a minimum of 36 hours;
2 - Prepare teaching resources for each class and provide relevant materials;
3 - Assess and evaluate students' work and provide a final course grade according to OISE/UT grading practices;
4 - Be available for informal meetings/communications with students as necessary.

qualifications_minimum:
1 - Candidate must have a doctoral degree in psychology or a related discipline;
2 - Individuals with demonstrated experience with related course content;
3- Prior experience teaching graduate courses preferred.

Ph.D in Anthropology (completed or in progress, preferably in Social Cultural Anthropology);
Strong background in medical anthropology;
Demonstrated evidence of superior teaching is required

qualifications_preferred:
2-3 years managing projects in an corporate setting;
familiarity with the Project Management Body Of Knowledge v8 and the Agile Practice Guide;
experience with the theory, tools and techniques used in Traditional Project Management and in Agile Project;
management either through work experience, completing courses or reviewing textbooks;
experience with case study analysis as a TA;
prior experience TAing a project management course; and
experience TAing a classes of 40-50 students with group and individual gradeable components.

duties:
a) Respond to student enquiries regarding MMA prerequisite assessments and preparation materials;
b) Provide clarification of the concepts in support of the assessments;
c) Monitor and respond to questions submitted through the online platform within the expected service timeframe;
d) Assist with matters related to the delivery and administration of the prerequisite assessments as required;
e) Other duties as assigned by the instructor.
